translate ru MarionPath3_0872c1ba:
    # "Sarah woke the next day."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_8755f1a9:
    # "Except for herself, the bed was empty."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_e598b99c:
    # "Light was already creeping through the curtains."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_6fe2e9eb:
    # "What time was it?"
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_39eb0230:
    # "She wondered where Marion could be. Likely busy, as he always appeared to be."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_ea1a6d8f:
    # "Sarah couldn't blame him."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_7bd84d17:
    # "There was a lot of work to be done."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_e1c5cb47:
    # "They had defeated the Tribes, but victory was not so clean."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_de8d30b2:
    # "Endless reports had begun to make their way to the capital, petitions urging Thomas to act."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_eccc6c50:
    # "For while the Capital had managed to repel the Tribes and break their army, the Eastern Provinces had not been so fortunate."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_b8b8b549:
    # "Many towns had been raided, pillaged, burned."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_babf9c1f:
    # "Reports told of entire towns, sometimes even cities, ruined."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_290946cf:
    # "Worse still, scouts often spoke of how few bodies they actually discovered among the ruins."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_6084ca4c:
    # "If a city was burned, one expected countless dead."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_45054e8d:
    # "Without the bodies, there was only one other troubling truth."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_b07c0880:
    # "Many of the inhabitants of the Eastern Provinces had suffered slavery at the hands of the Tribes."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_70e8a15e:
    # "Some had been freed, after the battle outside the Capital, but many were not accounted for."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_e154a4b3:
    # "Sons. Daughters. Wives. Carried off in chains to Gods knew where."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_e7d94c9e:
    # "Their farms, burned. Their cattle, killed and left to rot in the sun."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_8e7e18aa:
    # "Those who had managed to escape the Tribes, had found their homes gone."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_53bf2564:
    # "They still had their lives, but such things were cheap when one had no money, family or home."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_ac344ab8:
    # "Some of these men and women had been farmers for generations, reaching back beyond even their grandparents."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_434449d9:
    # "All the certainty of their lives had been wiped away."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_7301a08e:
    # "The cities of Rosanna were swelling with refugees."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_c0e68a7f:
    # "And as was so often the case, those who still had something, resented and feared those who now had nothing."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_0e6fa5db:
    # "For in them, they saw their own worst fears reflected."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_809defc2:
    # "That they were not all so different, and that they likewise lived upon the edge between surviving and ruin."
    ""

translate ru MarionPath3_4360bce5:
    # "For now, this is where the story ends."
    ""

